Script,BasicOvercall
window.currentPBSScenario = 'BasicOvercall';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Basic_Overcall';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for BasicOvercall');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'BasicOvercall',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: 21GF-NoInvertedMinor
convention-card-ew: 21GF-GIB
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1[CDHS] +1[DHSN]
*/
# East opens any 1-of-suit (12-21 HCP)
eHcp = hcp(east) > 11 and hcp(east) < 22
eShape = clubs(east) > 2 or diamonds(east) > 3 or spades(east) > 4 or hearts(east) > 4
eastHand = eHcp and eShape

# South overcalls: 8-16 HCP, 5+ in the overcalled suit
sHcp   = hcp(south) > 7 and hcp(south) < 17
sSuit  = spades(south) > 4 or hearts(south) > 4 or diamonds(south) > 4 or clubs(south) > 4
southHand = sHcp and sSuit

# Quiet partners (W passes since we're showing E opens; N's response after
# overcall is the user-learning part; don't pre-restrict).
wHcp = hcp(west) < 11

eastHand and southHand and wHcp

action printoneline,
average "East opens 1C   " 100 * (clubs(east) > 2 and clubs(east) >= diamonds(east) and hearts(east) < 5 and spades(east) < 5),
average "East opens 1D   " 100 * (diamonds(east) > 3 and diamonds(east) > clubs(east) and hearts(east) < 5 and spades(east) < 5),
average "East opens 1H   " 100 * (hearts(east) > 4 and spades(east) < 5),
average "East opens 1S   " 100 * (spades(east) > 4),
average "South HCP avg   "       hcp(south),
`, "E", true)
Script
Button,Basic Overcall,\n\
--- Basic Overcall (beginner)\n\
East (or West) opens 1!C，1!D，1!H，or 1!S. South — sitting next — makes\n\
a non-jump suit overcall at the 1- or 2-level (no 1NT overcall，no jumps,\n\
no two-suiters).\n\
\n\
A simple overcall is:\n\
• 8-16 HCP (lighter at the 1-level，more at the 2-level)\n\
• 5+ cards in the overcalled suit，headed by at least two honors\n\
• Sometimes lighter for lead direction (e.g.，1!C — 1!H is common with\n\
  a fair 5-card heart suit)\n\
\n\
For beginners: an overcall is a constructive bid showing a real suit and\n\
respectable values. It is NOT a takeout double，NOT a jump，NOT a 1NT\n\
overcall (which shows 15-18 with a stopper). Just a plain natural call.\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/overcalls.php\n\
%BasicOvercall%
